calculateHeading

public void calculateHeading()
Calculates the heading of the Airplane on this Edge.
 Taken from: http://mathforum.org/library/drmath/view/55417.html

 dlat &eq; lat2 - lat1
 dlon &eq; lon2 - lon1
 y &eq; sin(lon2-lon1)*cos(lat2)
 x &eq; cos(lat1)*sin(lat2)-sin(lat1)*cos(lat2)*cos(lon2-lon1)
 if y > 0 then
     if x > 0 then tc1 = arctan(y/x)
     if x < 0 then tc1 = 180 - arctan(-y/x)
     if x &eq; 0 then tc1 = 90
 if y < 0 then
     if x > 0 then tc1 = -arctan(-y/x)
     if x < 0 then tc1 = arctan(y/x)-180
     if x &eq; 0 then tc1 = 270
 if y &eq; 0 then
     if x > 0 then tc1 = 0
     if x < 0 then tc1 = 180
     if x &eq; 0 then [the 2 points are the same]
